Title: Acute central cervical spinal cord syndrome treated by acupuncture and electrical stimulation (AES).
Abstract: Twelve cases of acute central cervical spinal cord syndrome were treated by acupuncture and electrical stimulation. The paraesthesia, as well as movements of the hand and upper extremities, were greatly improved immediately after each treatment.
